# Reaching private instances

## Elastic IP

Static IPv4 you own; **survives stops**, **remaps** in minutes (failover). For **fixed-IP** needs (NAT, VPN, on-prem allowlist) — not app servers (use an LB).

## VPC DNS — two toggles

**enableDnsSupport** (AWS resolver → Route 53 private zones) · **enableDnsHostnames** (public DNS names). Both **on** in default VPC, **off** in custom. Route 53 Resolver bridges on-prem DNS.

## Flow Logs

Packet **metadata** (src/dst, port, **ACCEPT/REJECT**) → S3 / CloudWatch. Ground truth for a **silently-dropping** SG/NACL.

## Getting a shell

Old: **bastion host**. Modern default: **SSM Session Manager** — no SSH port, no public subnet, no key, audited.
